pacman::p_load("data.table", "dplyr")         

UB   <- fread(paste(getwd(),"Universal Bank_Main.csv", sep="/")) %>%       #  
   data.frame() %>%                                                     # Data frame 
   mutate(Personal.Loan = ifelse(Personal.Loan==1, "yes","no")) %>%     # Character for classification
   select(-1)                                                           # ID 


# select columns
cols <- c("Family", "Education", "Personal.Loan", "Securities.Account", 
          "CD.Account", "Online", "CreditCard")

UB   <- UB %>% 
  mutate_at(cols, as.factor)                                            #

2. 

# Partition (Traning Data : Test Data = 7:3)

pacman::p_load("caret")

y      <- UB$Personal.Loan                            # Target
 
set.seed(200)
ind    <- createDataPartition(y, p=0.7, list=T)       # Training Data 70% 

UB.trd <- UB[ind$Resample1,]                          # Traning Data


UB.ted <- UB[-ind$Resample1,]                         # Test Data

3. Method rpart


3-1.

Turn Parameter CP . . (caret xval = 0, cp .)

fitControl <- trainControl(method="cv", number=5)    # 5-fold-cross validation

set.seed(100)                                        # seed  for cross validation


rtree.caret <- train(Personal.Loan~., data=UB.trd, method="rpart", trControl = fitControl)

3-3-2. ROC


1) Package pROC

pacman::p_load("pROC")

test.rtree.prob <- predict(rtree.grid.caret, newdata = UB.ted, type="prob")  #  Training Data    Test Data     

test.rtree.prob <- test.rtree.prob[,2]                                       # "yes"   


ac             <- UB.ted$Personal.Loan                                       #         NApp             <- as.numeric(test.rtree.prob)                                # "yes"   

tree.roc       <- roc(ac, pp, plot = T, col = "red")                         # roc( ,  ))

auc            <- round(auc(tree.roc),3)
legend("bottomright",legend=auc, bty="n")

detach(package:pROC)


2) Package Epi

pacman::p_load("devtools", "Epi")
# install_version("etm", version = "1.1", repos = "http://cran.us.r-project.org")

ROC(pp, ac, plot="ROC")    # ROC( ,  ) /  cutoff value  

detach(package:Epi)


3) Package ROCR

pacman::p_load("ROCR")                                                  

rtree.pred <- prediction(test.rtree.prob, UB.ted$Personal.Loan) # prediction( ,  )     


rtree.perf <- performance(rtree.pred, "tpr", "fpr")             # performance(, "", "1-")")

plot(rtree.perf, col="red")                                     # ROC Curve

perf.auc        <- performance(rtree.pred, "auc")               # AUC
auc             <- attributes(perf.auc)$y.values
legend("bottomright", legend=auc, bty="n")

plot(rtree.perf, main="lift curve", colorize=T, lwd=2)

4-2. Tree

caret C5.0 plot . Tune Parameter Package C50 . caret C50 .

pacman::p_load("C50", "MASS","partykit")  

set.seed(100)
c5model = C5.0(x = UB.trd[,-9], y = UB.trd$Personal.Loan,
                       trials = ctree.grid.caret$bestTune$trials, rules = ctree.grid.caret$bestTune$model == "rules",
                       control = C5.0Control(winnow = ctree.grid.caret$bestTune$winnow))

c5model.pred          <- predict(c5model, newdata=UB.ted, type="prob")           # C50   

ctree.grid.caret.pred <- predict(ctree.grid.caret, newdata=UB.ted,type="prob")   # Caret   

sum(c5model.pred[,1]==ctree.grid.caret.pred[,1]) == dim(UB.ted)[1]               #      NA
[1] TRUE
c5model.pred          <- predict(c5model, newdata=UB.ted)                        # C50     

ctree.grid.caret.pred <- predict(ctree.grid.caret, newdata=UB.ted)               # Caret   

sum(c5model.pred==ctree.grid.caret.pred) == dim(UB.ted)[1]                       #      NA
[1] TRUE
plot(c5model)

ac             <- UB.ted$Personal.Loan                                       #         NApp             <- as.numeric(test.ctree.prob)                                # "yes"

auc            <- round(auc(tree.roc),3)
legend("bottomright",legend=auc, bty="n")
